        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 4:57PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 456 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles southeast of The Intersection Of Us 190 And Highway 163, or 10
miles northeast of Ozona, moving southwest at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and very heavy rainfall

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Ozona.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
